<br>
Let me state first that I do know and have known some very decent druids who played their class well and were welcome in my groups.<br>
<br>
But the trend I've seen recently, is almost every druid I've grouped/duoed with in the past 2 weeks is a complete utter moron when it comes to playing their class.  This is just my opinion remember, others might not see such a big deal with my grypes.  But in my opinion its just pure idiocy.<br>
<br>
Issue #1: When a druid decides to go pull a mob, why do they run on top of the mob so they get hit, THEN try to cast snare on it ? Wouldn't the logical solution be to just snare from max range and run back ? I think I've seen about 20 druids in the past week pull this way.<br>
<br>
Issue #2: Mob is back at camp spot, druid insists on running on top of the mob in order to root/ cast snare on it.  Snare has large aggro, and as a result of being on top of the mob, the druid gets pounded. Said druid then proceeds to complain about how they get so much aggro.  I witnessed 5 different druids in the past week do just this.<br>
<br>
Issue #3: I don't think I have ever seen a class die as much as druids, well at least lately in my opinion.  I die in groups and solo on average once a week. I am a mage, i have ZERO defense.  Yet I see druids soloing and dying left and right, and dying with me while duoing.  How the hell is that possible ???<br>
<br>
Druids have snare, always have sow up, and now with SOE have lev up usually all the time, I could see &quot;maybe&quot; if someone dropped 20 mobs on them and they got hit all at once they would die.  But how in the world can a druid die while soloing one mob ?? I mean if you go oom and root breaks, just run moron.  If you get an add, just run.  I mean come on, are these people retarded ?<br>
<br>
I played a friends level 56 druid for awhile once to farm supplies and had the most fun of my life and can't even imagine how a druid can die so easily soloing.  I was in scarlett desert tracking named to the middle of the zone with mobs all over, breaking invis, snaring it, dotting it, then just reinvising and sitting in the middle of the zone watching it die.  If an add ever came, I just ran a bit, snared it, rooted it etc... I mean its not rocket science, or maybe it is ???<br>
<br>
Issue #4 Druids in POD thinking its smart to fight mobs in the middle of mob infested areas.  Case in point, most people solo/duo or group along the left wall by pulling mobs TO the wall.  I was soloing the other day and saw this druid out in the middle of the area killing a goo with her charmed rat while mobs were all around.  Then I saw 2 mobs aggro her (duh) and her die.  Are you really that stupid ?<br>
<br>
Issue #5 Druids and charm.  Druids can charm animals and they can also give their pets commands, pet back off, pet attack, pet follow me, pet guard here.  Why is it that druids will sit right next to their pet while medding ??? If it was DC'd I could understand.  But you have a regular charmed mob that charm could break on at any moment, and you decide to sit right next to it to med ?? I've witnessed 5 druid deaths in the past week due to this idiocy.<br>
<br>
Even after telling druids hey tell your pet to guard here, then just move a good distance away from it in case charm breaks.  They still sit right on top of it, arghhh.<br>
<br>
Also, duoing at a camp with druid, charm breaks, druid runs to get distance to snare/charm.  Instead of running along the wall of the zone, I've seen so many druids run right out into the mob infested area to try and get away from their charmed mob, and 90% of the time, they get aggro from a new mob and die.  Are they that stupid ???<br>
<br>
Also I know how to aggro kite, and when I do, I get hit every now and then when mob is chasing me and i stop to get a nuke off before it catches up to me, it happens.  But what I've seen lately is it seems like druids simply have no concept of distance, and casting time.  For instance charm breaks, druid runs 10 feet out into middle of mob infested area stops, turns around and tries to snare.  THe druid takes like 10 steps, the second he stops, the mob is on him beating him like crazy, yet he still tries to snare.  He gets interupted usually, then tries it again, 10 steps, stop tuirn around, snare. Dead druid...<br>
<br>
I mean what in the world is so hard about running and getting a good distance on a mob before you stop and try to cast ? Its not that difficult.  <br>
<br>
Issue #6: Duoing in POD with druid, he goes out to find a rat.  Diseased seem to be the best from my experience because charm holds good it seems.  Pestillent always seemed to high of level to charm.  Anway druid knows this info.  <br>
