<br>
<br>
3. Those Druids die because they don't think. They don't think ahead, they don't know all the options available to them if they get into hot water. They truly don't know how close to indestructible they can be-they don't pay attention to their surroundings, they don't look at pathing, other people, etc etc. And unfortunately, tho they die and die and die, they are still powerful enough to somehow get into their 50's without knowing more than a few dimensions of their class. <br>
<br>
